Thought: To determine if a number is prime, we can check if it has any divisors other than 1 and itself. We'll iterate through numbers from 2 up to the square root of the input number, checking for divisibility. If we find any divisor, it's not prime.

```ruby
def is_prime?(num)
  return false if num <= 1
  
  (2..Math.sqrt(num)).none? { |i| num % i == 0 }
end

final_answer(answer: is_prime?(17))
```
